The evidence with the title 'Poverty level under Obama breaks 50-year record - Washington Times ' says Jan 7, 2014  ... Fifty years after president Johnson started a $ 20 trillion taxpayer-funded war on poverty , the overall percentage of impoverished people in the U.S. has declined only slightly and the poor have lost ground  ... A record 47 million Americans receive food stamps , about 13 million more than when he took office . 
